<!-- unified-memory start -->
## Memory

This project uses unified-memory for persistent context across sessions.

- On session start: read MEMORY.md and .memory/CONTINUATION.md if present
- On session end: update MEMORY.md with decisions, blockers, active work, and where we left off
- Run `umem doctor` to check memory health
- Run `umem compact` to compress memory when it grows large
- Never store secrets, passwords, tokens, or API keys in memory files
- Strip <private>...</private> blocks before persisting anything
<!-- unified-memory end -->
